=9D probably you have a duty to keep that information confidential, and if =
you trade on it that=E2=80=99s a crime. But if you are just some random per=
son sitting at the next table and you=C2=A0<em>overhear </em>her saying tha=
t, you have no duty of trust and confidence to her, and you <a href=3D"http=
s://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/35548615.259324/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuY=
