uietly buys some stock =E2=80=94=C2=A0a =E2=80=9Ctoehold=E2=80=9D =E2=80=94=
=C2=A0before making the proposal public, that=E2=80=99s probably fine: The =
acquirer has no inside information=C2=A0<em>about the company</em>; it only=
 has inside information=C2=A0<em>about its own plans</em>, and can do what =
it wants with those. Warren Buffett=E2=80=99s Berkshire Hathaway Inc. is al=
lowed to buy a stake in a company and then announce that stake, rather than=
 the reverse; it is allowed to trade knowing its own intentions.=C2=A0</li>=
